{"id":"2209.14925","submitter":"Jonathan Fruchter","authors":"Jonathan Fruchter and Ismael Morales","title":"Virtual homology of residually free groups and profinite rigidity of\n  direct products","comments":"43 pages, 4 figures, comments are welcome. Generalized previous\n  results; added result on profinite rigidty of direct products","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR math.GT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We show that the virtual second Betti number of a finitely generated,\nresidually free group $G$ is finite if and only if $G$ is either free, free\nabelian or the fundamental group of a closed surface. We continue and calculate\nthe virtual Betti numbers of limit groups in all dimensions. We also develop\ntechniques involving rank gradients of pro-$p$ groups, which allow us to\nrecognize direct product decompositions. Combining the above ideas, we show\nthat direct products of free and surface groups are profinitely rigid among\nfinitely presented, residually free groups, partially resolving a conjecture of\nBridson's. Other corollaries that we obtain include a confirmation of\nMel'nikov's surface group conjecture in the residually free case, and a\ndescription of closed aspherical manifolds of dimension at least $5$ with a\nresidually free fundamental group.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Sep 2022 16:43:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 May 2023 17:01:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-25"}
